{"build_type":"library","description":"Native (pure-IPM, Variant-A) lowering DISPATCH ROUTER (#33 VARIANT A): thin replacement for the 92KB monolith lower_one_instruction_into_native_ops. Reads inst[instruction_type] via inst_field_string and dispatches to one per-type handler lower_<type>_to_native_ops(inst, ops); each handler emits its low-ops into the shared ops array via native-lowering-emit-helpers (begin_native_low_op_object / add_string_to_object / add_number_to_object). The recursive handlers (conditional_branch / for_count_loop / while_loop) call BACK into this router to lower nested body instructions -- mutual recursion router<->handler (a call-graph cycle the closed-graph + fixup resolution handles, proven with the 66-fn renderer). Splitting the monolith per-type also dissolves the tracked 256-slot frame overflow. Depends on native-lowering-emit-helpers and the 14 per-type handler packages. The instruction-array walking and self-tail-call optimization live in native-lower-self-tail-call.","module_name":"choose-lowering-routine-across-instruction","package_name":"choose-lowering-routine-across-instruction","function_definitions":{"choose-lowering-routine-across-instruction":{"return_type":"void","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"inst","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"ops","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"key_itype","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"instruction_type"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"itype","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"extract-instruction-field-string-value","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"inst"},{"kind":"var","value":"key_it